co.herxun.lscordova
Class LightspeedPushPlugin

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.cordova.api.CordovaPlugin
      co.herxun.lscordova.LightspeedPushPlugin

public class LightspeedPushPlugin
extends org.apache.cordova.api.CordovaPlugin

Lightspeed push Cordova Plugin. Below document describes the steps you need to do for register Lightspeed Push channels.

1. With the action string LightspeedPushPlugin.PushConstants.ActionSet.INITIALIZE_PUSH, initialize a push instance.
2. If you're using built-in Lightspeed push, a Lightspeed server status monitor is necessary.
With action string LightspeedPushPlugin.PushConstants.ActionSet.STATUS_MONITOR you could implement a callback function to monitor the status.
3. Register corresponding channels with action string LightspeedPushPlugin.PushConstants.ActionSet.REGISTER
4. Implement a callback function as receiving push with action string LightspeedPushPlugin.PushConstants.ActionSet.RECV_PUSH
5. ( Optional ) You could implement other feature of Push with the rest action string. For example, LightspeedPushPlugin.PushConstants.ActionSet.SET_MUTE set the device receiving push without system alarm.


For more detail information, please refer to the LightspeedPushPlugin.PushConstants.ActionSet to see what you can do with this plug-in.

Herxun
